properties.name: May 1st, 1860: Hudson's Bay Company, Fort Vancouver
properties.description:
Wilson arrives at Fort Vancouver, the Hudson's Bay Company's former regional headquarters. John McAdoo Work is in charge. The fort is surrounded by American troops under the command of General Harney, but relations are cordial. "This is a sweetly pretty place." 

Accuracy: HIGHLY LIKELY.

properties.name: May 16th, 1860: The Dalles
properties.description:
Wilson arrives at the Dalles at 10:30 p.m. by steamboat from the Upper Cascades. He stays here at Umatilla House until June 1st, when he has to return to Fort Vancouver and Portland to bring up a lot of money. He gets back with over 2000 in gold on June 6th, 1860.

According to http://www.historicthedalles.org/history/umatilla_house.htm, "The Umatilla House was located on the Northeast corner of First (then called "Main") and Union streets."

Accuracy: HIGHLY LIKELY.

properties.name: May 16th, 1860: Lower Cascades of the Columbia
properties.description:
Steamboat from Fort Vancouver brings Wilson to the Lower Cascasdes, where he disembarks at about 2:30 p.m. and walks 4.5 miles upstream to the Upper Cascades. Baggage is transpoted in wagons. He describes flowers in bloom and Indians fishing for salmon.

He will pass through here again on June 1st (downbound) and June 6th (upbound again).

Accuracy: GUESSED.

properties.name: May 16th, 1860: Upper Cascades of the Columbia
properties.description:
Wilson departs the Upper Cascades for the Dalles at 4 p.m. by steamboat.

He passes through here again on June 1st (downstream) and June 6th (upstream again).

Accuracy: GUESSED.

properties.name: May 16th, 1860: portage around the cascades of the Columbia
properties.description:
Wilson passed through here again on June 1st (downstream) and June 6th (upstream, and this time carrying ₤2000 in gold).

Accuracy: GUESSED.

properties.name: May 16th, 1860: by steamboat to the  Lower Cascades of the Columbia
properties.description:
Wilson departs on the steamer Carrie Ladd (Oregon Steam Navigation Company) at about 8:30 in the morning. 

He repeates this jounrey downbound on June 1st, and upbound again on June 6th.

Accuracy: GUESSED.

properties.name: May 16th, 1860: by steamship to The Dalles
properties.description:
This boat takes from 4 p.m. to 10:30 p.m.

Wilson reversed this journey on June 1st, 1860, and then comes back up again on June 6th.

Accuracy: GUESSED.
